roject success. The thinking also hints at how modern interactive tools using JavaScript are becoming relevant to this process. I'm noticing that the knowledge file jumps straight into the bullet points about mockup issues, but the source material includes important context explaining why dynamic screen-based specification agreement is critical to project success. This background reasoning about the framework's design philosophy could be useful when explaining Nablarch's approach to users, though it's not strictly necessary for implementation guidance.\n\nLooking at the multi-browser problem section, the source describes how traditional development locked in specific OS/browser versions for testing, but smartphone and tablet support became mandatory across most projects, making it impractical to verify behavior across all devices within realistic timelines.\n\nNow examining the fabrication check section where the knowledge base notes that showing customers actual screens risks derailing specification work with appearance-focused discussions unrelated to functionality. 次のセクション構造を確認しているが、RST形式での見出しレベルの定義が明確でない。ソース内容と照合しながら、各セクションが正しく対応しているかを検証する必要がある。 to 9 h3 sections from the first two h2 sections, plus the 3rd h2 section as a single section since it has no h3 subdivisions—that accounts for the 7 total sections in the knowledge file.\n\nLooking at the section lengths, s4 and s6 both meet the minimum character threshold, though s6 appears to be cut off mid-sentence.\n\nThe IDs are sequential across all seven sections, which checks out.\n\nFor the hints, since this is conceptual documentation rather than API reference material, there aren't class names or annotations to reference, so what's there seems appropriate.\n\nBut reviewing s1 more carefully, I'm noticing it's missing some important context from the source material about the broader role of screen mockups in the external design phase and how they're used in specifications with tools like Excel.\n\nFor s4, there's also a gap—the source explains how traditional development processes fixed OS and browser versions and tested each one separately, which provides the foundation for understanding why the responsive approach matters.\n\nThese feel more like explanatory background than decision-critical information, so they're probably minor omissions rather than structural problems. I'm identifying the key omissions in the knowledge file compared to the source material. The intro paragraph listing the three main features of Nablarch UI is essentially a navigation outline, so that's acceptable to skip. But I'm finding substantive context gaps—particularly in the 問題点 section where the reasoning about why mockups matter (Excel-based specs, customer comprehension issues, the importance of working screens) gets lost, and similarly in the マルチブラウザ section where the traditional approach explanation is missing. These are more significant contextual losses than just navigation elements.\n\nLooking at this from what an AI would need to answer user questions effectively, that introductory reasoning does add value—someone asking why the framework creates JSP at the design stage would benefit from understanding the underlying problem context. Though I notice some of this reasoning does surface in the メリット section, so it's not entirely absent. I'm marking these as minor omissions overall, since the knowledge file captures the core information reasonably well despite these gaps.\n\nThe s1 issue is more significant though—the 問題点 section in the source has both introductory paragraphs and bullet points, but the knowledge file only includes the bullet points. That's a real loss of context about the framework's motivation, even if it's background material. And s4 similarly drops the context about traditional development approaches and version constraints. These are the kinds of details an AI would need to properly explain the framework's reasoning.\n\nBoth are minor omissions in terms of severity—they're contextual background rather than critical constraints or implementation details—but they're worth noting as gaps in the knowledge base.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17927,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":17927,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ca3b17d4-5921-42d8-a829-01912a6d4ed2","uuid":"7813c29b-a443-4cd3-9968-e5db908086cc"}
